               <p>I live in Skinners-street, in the Strand: on Tuesday evening, the 10th of December, as I was coming out of <placeName id="t17770115-10-crimeloc53">Drury Lane theatre</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17770115-10-crimeloc53" type="placeName" value="Drury Lane theatre"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17770115-10-crimeloc53" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17770115-10-off51 t17770115-10-crimeloc53"></join>, I missed my watch; I immediately seized the prisoner by his arm; I saw the watch in his hand; he attempted to give it to another person, and the watch fell; I took the watch off the pavement with one hand, and held the prisoner with the other; the outer case fell off, which I have never recovered.</p>
               <p>Did you feel the prisoner at the time he took it away? - Yes, I felt his hand very distinctly, his back was towards me as he drew it out; I saw the chain in his hand.</p>
               <p>From the Prisoner. Whether he did not cry stop thief, after another person, but I being the poorest person near him he challenged me with it? - I did not call stop thief.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17770115-10-verdict54" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17770115-10-verdict54" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>Tried by the First Middlesex Jury before Mr. Justice ASHHURST.</p>
